A '''cade''' was a [[cask]] or [[barrel]], used in the British [[Book of Rates]] for a determinate number of some sort of [[fish]]. For example, a cade of [[herring]]s was a vessel containing the quantity of 500 herrings; a cade of [[sprat]]s contained 1,000.

